column5: I'm good to go for another 2 years so,,,,I got mine

I just bite the bullet renew for 3 yrs one more to go.$144.00 cause I live outside Ontario.  Too many times I would buy at the last minute and scramble to find a place that sells it.Now its on line and for 3yrs.  On the bright side my Quebec licence is good until March 31st 2011.
Got to pick up my 2011 fishing lic.Whos selling them now?  Bash me if you may ,but remember,paybacksapain.
Cant believe I got away with that word.LOL  Well almost did.
I just picked mine up today at LeBarons in Markham.  Cheers, Colin
Mine's good 'till Dec 2012 !  Leah and Jen's .. in the mail...  Local CTC should have them by now??? or try calling Backwater Tackle in Midland... seeing you're coming up here Friday anyhow!
Yaaa didn't  Art
DANG.. Art's figgered out the Moderator button !
you can only get the 1 year license that way. the only way to get the 3 year is online or at 1 of the mnr office's.
I am,,,,,,,,,oh ya, I am.   Saddly Art,I didnt have one for this 2010 year.  Time to back at er.  CTC, here I come.   Fine with me Skeeter. One year at a time they say.
OK OK OK,Who edited?????????

I was at the CTC in the south end of Barrie a few days ago and they said they wouldn't have any until the new year....but I heard through the grapevine that Robinson's Hardware in the northeast side of Barrie has them.  The only reason I got mine at LeBarons is because I work close by.  Colin
Thanks for the reminder, just picked mine up from the hall closet, put it there about 3 weeks ago when it came in the mail, it has found its spot in the wallet.
LOL

Funny,they always seem to have them.Of all the places in Barrie,Robertsons always was first.They even still have a great supply of boating stuff.Weather it be small or yuaht stuff.  Thanks for the heads up Colin.   As for that Angus guy,,,,,,,,,,,,

Brian, I ordered my 3 year Sportfishing license, Outdoors card, and...............for the first time ever............my 3 year Small Game License!!!  Did it all online after making a trip to the local Service Ontario office to upgrade my status to include hunting.  Came to $159.00+!!!!! Considered going with the conservation version, but changed my mind at the last minute

Dang MR B,I forgot you were taking the course at the wolfsden.Sry bud I didnt get out to say howdy. Im feel like a dumb :asshat:lot,s of work.Mind goes crazy,but Im back to my olself now,,,,,,,,,,,I thunk.  Good on ya for getting yer hunting lic bud.

I got my card about 2 months ago from Canada's MNR I put it into my glove box in the Titan so when I come up I can get my license to fish. The Fishing license we have here can be bought on line also and is good from the date purchased one year later.  Art
got mine in the mail already  a few weeks back, good for another 3 years

Do yer math.I didnt fish last year,so if I bought a three year 2007-2010,I would of lost money..... Never one that was for the the 3 yr lic. One never knows.It,s not like our money is really doing anything. Well,it does,it lets us fish and hunt,but,,,,,,,We have already been down that road,havent we

I tried to buy at south side barrie ctc and they said not until at least 1st week of jan.  I went online to renew card and get one year licence but I could not get a one year and was forced to get a 3 year.  I know it is a better deal but was not in the budget.  Oh well, always easier to ask for forgiveness then ask for permission. PS.  Glad to hear you are going to get out this year.  Make it a priority!
I got my Seniors card. That means I never need to buy a fishing license again.
Does sprawl-mart have them in stock yet? Not that it matters unless I'm getting the boat out this weekend with all the warm weather coming.
Well stopped by Robinsons hardware this morning.They had the lic in.Bought one,and to boot headed up to Penatang,picked up a new to me PE1 portable hut.Thanks Wayne.
I did the online renewal even before my notice came from the MNR.  My 3 year fishing and small game arrived in the mail the first of December.
